mbrSWRev.name: mbrSWRev
mbrSWRev.description: Major release number of the current software image

mbrSWRel.name: mbrSWRel
mbrSWRel.description: Minor release number of the current software image

mbrSWTstVers.name: mbrSWTstVers
mbrSWTstVers.description: Internal test release number of the current software image

mbrSWSpecial.name: mbrSWSpecial
mbrSWSpecial.description: 'Customer Special' release number of the current software image

mbrBootDate.name: mbrBootDate
mbrBootDate.description: Date of last system boot in an opaque format. When the value is represented as a four-byte number in canonical form with byte 0 being the most significant, then the following is true: bytes 0-1: two-byte number is the year value byte 2: one-byte number is the month value byte 3: one-byte number is the day of the month

mbrBootTime.name: mbrBootTime
mbrBootTime.description: Hour of last system boot in an opaque format. When the value is represented as a four-byte number in canonical form with byte 0 being the most significant, then the following is true: byte 0: one-byte number is the hour (1-24) byte 1: one-byte number is the minute (0-59) byte 2: one-byte number is the second (0-59) byte 3: has no significance

mbrArchCfgStr.name: mbrArchCfgStr
mbrArchCfgStr.description: Archived (backup) config string. This corresponds to the file bridge.bak. Each instance of this object corresponds to a fixed size record that is a portion of the entire configuration string. The integer index identifies the logical record accessed in the config string.

mbrCurCfgStr.name: mbrCurCfgStr
mbrCurCfgStr.description: Current config string--This config will be read and used the next time the mbr restarts. This corresponds to the file bridge.cfg. Each instance of this object corresponds to a fixed size record that is a portion of the entire configuration string. The integer index identifies the logical record accessed in the config string. After writing a new mbrCurCfgStr, use mbrCtrlCmd(8) to save the string to the MBR's disk.

mbrRunCfgStr.name: mbrRunCfgStr
mbrRunCfgStr.description: Running config string--The config the mbr used when it was last started. This corresponds to the file bridge.run. Each instance of this object corresponds to a fixed size record that is a portion of the entire configuration string. The integer index identifies the logical record accessed in the config string.

mbrSysAddress.name: mbrSysAddress
mbrSysAddress.description: System MAC Address. Corresponds to the MAC address of one of the LAN ports present in the MBR.

mbrConfigRec.name: mbrConfigRec
mbrConfigRec.description: Number of logical configuration records in a config string (of size 400 octets). The integer index value is one of the following: 1: mbrArchCfgStr, 2: mbrCurCfgStr, 3: mbrRunCfgStr

mbrSysName.name: mbrSysName
mbrSysName.description: This object is identical to sysName. It corresponds to the contents of the MBR file name.dat

mbrSysPasswd.name: mbrSysPasswd
mbrSysPasswd.description: The system password. A read of this object results with a zero length string. Note that a control session is required to write this object. The maximum allowed length of this object is 32 octets

mbrDesigRootAddr.name: mbrDesigRootAddr
mbrDesigRootAddr.description: The MAC address of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol executing on this bridge.

mbrDesigRootPriority.name: mbrDesigRootPriority
mbrDesigRootPriority.description: The priority value of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol executing on this bridge

mbrRootPathCost.name: mbrRootPathCost
mbrRootPathCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge

mbrRootPort.name: mbrRootPort
mbrRootPort.description: A string that describes the port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge

mbrCtrlRequester.name: mbrCtrlRequester
mbrCtrlRequester.description: A unique string submitted by a manager when attempting to establish a control session. When a control session has been established, this value is copied to mbrSessPartner. The MAC address of the requesting manager is typically used (because it is unique). This object should be included first in each set-request that attempts to modify mbrSessionFlag, and objects in the mbrSysControl group.

mbrCtrlPasswd.name: mbrCtrlPasswd
mbrCtrlPasswd.description: The password value submitted for verification when attempting to establish a control session. Verification is performed by comparing this value to mbrSysPasswd. An exact match is required for verification (and control session establishment). NULL is a valid value.

mbrCtrlCmd.name: mbrCtrlCmd
mbrCtrlCmd.description: Writing this object causes an action to be taken by the MBR. The action taken corresponds to the value submitted by the manager. Control commands consist of the following values: -verifyPassword(1): compares mbrCtrlPasswd to mbrSysPasswd. If exact match, then mbrCtrlRequester is copied to mbrSessPartner and control session is established. -systemBoot(2): initiates a system boot if control session is active. -requestDownload(3): performs a file operation on mbrDlFileName. The operation is specified by mbrCtrlParm. -clearAlarms(4): clears the MBR alarm table. -clearStats(5): resets the statistics on the MBR port corresponding to mbrCtrlPort. -updateConfig(8): This command causes mbrCurCfgStr to copied into mbrArchCfgStr and saves mbrCurCfgStr to the MBR's disk. Use this command after writing a new mbrCurCfgStr.

mbrCtrlPort.name: mbrCtrlPort
mbrCtrlPort.description: The port number value submitted by a manager to be referenced in conjunction with port-specific actions defined by mbrCtrlCmd values. This value must be set when mbrCtrlCmd is set to clearStats(6).

mbrCtrlParm.name: mbrCtrlParm
mbrCtrlParm.description: This object qualifies the download operation requested when mbrCtrlCmd is requestDownload(3). The valid download operations are: 0: open file mbrDlFileName for reading, 1: open file mbrDlFileName for writing, 2: close file mbrDlFileName

mbrSessionFlag.name: mbrSessionFlag
mbrSessionFlag.description: This object is true when a control session is active on this MBR. The control session partner may write a value of false to terminate the control session. The session is terminated only if mbrSessionPartner is exactly equal to mbrCtrlRequester.

mbrSessionPartner.name: mbrSessionPartner
mbrSessionPartner.description: This object identifies the control session partner. It is copied from the value of mbrCtrlRequester when a control session is established.

mbrDlStatus.name: mbrDlStatus
mbrDlStatus.description: This object denotes the state of the current download operation as follows: 0: download complete, 3: download progressing, 4: disk error occurred

mbrDlReadRec.name: mbrDlReadRec
mbrDlReadRec.description: Each instance of this object corresponds to one fixed size record in the file mbrDlFileName. The integer index identifies the logical record accessed in mbrDlFileName. This object can be read only after mbrDlFileName has been opened for reading.

mbrDlWriteRec.name: mbrDlWriteRec
mbrDlWriteRec.description: Each instance of this object corresponds to one fixed size record in the file mbrDlFileName. The integer index identifies the logical record written to in mbrDlFileName. This object can be set only after mbrDlFileName has been opened for writing. The records must be written in order. Reading this object returns an octet string of length zero

mbrDlFileSize.name: mbrDlFileSize
mbrDlFileSize.description: This object provides the number of records in mbrDlFileName. It is calculated by the MBR when mbrDlFileName is opened (for reading or writing). The fixed record size is 1024 octets.

mbrAlarmEntry.name: mbrAlarmEntry
mbrAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the MBR alarm table. The integer index corresponds to the MBR alarm code.

mbrAlarmText.name: mbrAlarmText
mbrAlarmText.description: The alarm text string that corresponds to the alarm instance represented by the current SNMP trap. Some alarm text strings contain printf-style format specifiers. The parameters that apply to the format specifiers are specified by the instances of mbrTrapInfo in the same SNMP trap.

mbrNetRptDestIpAddress.name: mbrNetRptDestIpAddress
mbrNetRptDestIpAddress.description: The IP address of a SNMP trap destination. A control session should be established before writing this object.

mbrTrapCode.name: mbrTrapCode
mbrTrapCode.description: This value is the MBR alarm code. An SNMP trap containing this object represents an instance of the MBR alarm.

mbrTrapPort.name: mbrTrapPort
mbrTrapPort.description: This value is the MBR port that an alarm has occurred on. Alarms that do not logically correspond to a port are assigned port number 1.

mbrTrapInfo.name: mbrTrapInfo
mbrTrapInfo.description: One or more parameters that apply to a specific MBR alarm. The integer index identifies the position of the parameter in the printf argument list. The argument list is formed by ordering all mbrTrapInfo instances in one SNMP trap. This argument list is applied to the accompanying mbrAlarmText printf format string.

mbrRmAlarmStatAddr.name: mbrRmAlarmStatAddr
mbrRmAlarmStatAddr.description: The MAC address of the Token Ring station that is experiencing a problem

mbrRmAlarmNaunAddr.name: mbrRmAlarmNaunAddr
mbrRmAlarmNaunAddr.description: The MAC address of the nearest active upstream neighbor (NAUN) of the Token Ring station that is experiencing a problem

mbrRmAlarmBeaconType.name: mbrRmAlarmBeaconType
mbrRmAlarmBeaconType.description: The value of the Beacon Type subvector in the last Beacon MAC frame received

mbrWifLinkState.name: mbrWifLinkState
mbrWifLinkState.description: This details the Spanning Tree Algorithm (STA) state of the port. When STA is off, the port may be either up, down, or disabled.

mbrWifLinkDelaySeconds.name: mbrWifLinkDelaySeconds
mbrWifLinkDelaySeconds.description: The seconds component of the round-trip link delay across the WAN port connection, including processing by the remote MBR.

mbrWifLinkDelayMillis.name: mbrWifLinkDelayMillis
mbrWifLinkDelayMillis.description: The milliseconds component of the round-trip link delay across a WAN port connection, including processing by the remote MBR.

mbrWifSppActiveCount.name: mbrWifSppActiveCount
mbrWifSppActiveCount.description: The number of active SPP connections for this WAN port. This number is updated by the MBR only when the 3Com protocol support option is enabled for this WAN port.

mbrWifLinkSpeed.name: mbrWifLinkSpeed
mbrWifLinkSpeed.description: The bandwith of the port in units of 100 bps. This object is equivalent to ifSpeed/100

mbrWifLinkChangeTime.name: mbrWifLinkChangeTime
mbrWifLinkChangeTime.description: Hour of last system boot in an opaque format. When the value is represented as a four-byte integer in canonical form with byte 0 being the most significant, then the following is true: byte 0: one-byte integer is the hour (1-24) byte 1: one-byte integer is the minute (0-59) byte 2: one-byte integer is the second (0-59) byte 3: has no significance

mbrWifLinkChangeDate.name: mbrWifLinkChangeDate
mbrWifLinkChangeDate.description: Date of last system boot in an opaque format. When the value is represented as a four-byte integer in canonical form with byte 0 being the most significant, then the following is true: bytes 0-1: two-byte integer is the year value byte 2: one-byte integer is the month value byte 3: one-byte integer is the day of the month

mbrWifLongTermStatsInterval.name: mbrWifLongTermStatsInterval
mbrWifLongTermStatsInterval.description: This object represents the current time interval that the MBR is using to track its long term statistics for this port.

mbrWifLoadShareSetId.name: mbrWifLoadShareSetId
mbrWifLoadShareSetId.description: This object is non-zero only if this port is a member of a set of load-sharing WAN ports. All members of a single set of load-sharing WAN ports share the same mbrWifLoadShareSetId (usually the lowest port number of the set)

mbrWifVcCount.name: mbrWifVcCount
mbrWifVcCount.description: The number of VCs configured for this port.

mbrWifVcCallState.name: mbrWifVcCallState
mbrWifVcCallState.description: The call state of this VC.

mbrWifVcDelaySeconds.name: mbrWifVcDelaySeconds
mbrWifVcDelaySeconds.description: The seconds component of the round-trip delay across the VC, including processing by the remote MBR.

mbrWifVcDelayMillis.name: mbrWifVcDelayMillis
mbrWifVcDelayMillis.description: The milliseconds component of the round-trip delay across the VC, including processing by the remote MBR.

mbrWifVcLongTermStatsInterval.name: mbrWifVcLongTermStatsInterval
mbrWifVcLongTermStatsInterval.description: This object represents the current time interval that the MBR is using to track its long term statistics for this VC.

mbrWifVcLcn.name: mbrWifVcLcn
mbrWifVcLcn.description: The LCN assigned to this VC

mbrWifVcRemoteDte.name: mbrWifVcRemoteDte
mbrWifVcRemoteDte.description: The DTE address to which this VC call is established

mbrWifStatTable.name: mbrWifStatTable
mbrWifStatTable.description: Table for short and long term WAN statistics

mbrWifStatEntry.name: mbrWifStatEntry
mbrWifStatEntry.description: An entry in the WAN statistics table. The first of the two integer index values specifies the relative time interval of the statistic value. Short term stats are measured over a sliding 128-second window. Long term stats are measured over the period specified by the WAN port's mbrWifLongTermStatsInterval. The second index value specifies the MBR WAN port.

mbrWifRcvChars.name: mbrWifRcvChars
mbrWifRcvChars.description: The number of octets received from this WAN port during the last stats interval.

mbrWifXmtChars.name: mbrWifXmtChars
mbrWifXmtChars.description: The number of octets transmitted from this WAN port during the last stats interval.

mbrWifRcvFrames.name: mbrWifRcvFrames
mbrWifRcvFrames.description: The number of HDLC frames received from this WAN port during the last stats interval.

mbrWifXmtFrames.name: mbrWifXmtFrames
mbrWifXmtFrames.description: The number of HDLC frames transmitted out this WAN port during the last stats interval.

mbrWifRcvBadFrames.name: mbrWifRcvBadFrames
mbrWifRcvBadFrames.description: The number of HDLC frames received with error during the last stats interval.

mbrWifXmtRejects.name: mbrWifXmtRejects
mbrWifXmtRejects.description: The number of HDLC frame rejects transmitted during the last stats interval.

mbrWifRcvRejects.name: mbrWifRcvRejects
mbrWifRcvRejects.description: The number of HDLC frame rejects received during the last stats interval.

mbrWifRexmtTimeouts.name: mbrWifRexmtTimeouts
mbrWifRexmtTimeouts.description: The number of retransmission timer timeouts occurrences during the last stats interval.

mbrWifLanPktsDiscarded.name: mbrWifLanPktsDiscarded
mbrWifLanPktsDiscarded.description: The number of LAN packets discarded due to lack of resources during the last stats interval.

mbrWifMgmtPktsForwarded.name: mbrWifMgmtPktsForwarded
mbrWifMgmtPktsForwarded.description: The number of proprietary link-management packets forwarded during the last stats interval.

mbrWifRcvCompRatio.name: mbrWifRcvCompRatio
mbrWifRcvCompRatio.description: The current ratio of raw octets to compressed octets received for this WAN connection. The index indicates the MBR port number.

mbrWifXmtCompRatio.name: mbrWifXmtCompRatio
mbrWifXmtCompRatio.description: The current ratio of raw octets to compressed octets transmitted for this WAN connection. The index indicates the MBR port number.

mbrWifRminCompRatio.name: mbrWifRminCompRatio
mbrWifRminCompRatio.description: The lowest ratio of raw octets to compressed octets received for this WAN connection. The index indicates the MBR port number.

mbrWifXminCompRatio.name: mbrWifXminCompRatio
mbrWifXminCompRatio.description: The lowest ratio of raw octets to compressed octets transmitted for this WAN connection. The index indicates the MBR port number.

mbrWifRmaxCompRatio.name: mbrWifRmaxCompRatio
mbrWifRmaxCompRatio.description: The highest ratio of raw octets to compressed octets received for this WAN connection. The index indicates the MBR port number.

mbrWifXmaxCompRatio.name: mbrWifXmaxCompRatio
mbrWifXmaxCompRatio.description: The highest ratio of raw octets to compressed octets transmitted for this WAN connection. The index indicates the MBR port number.

mbrWifVcStatTable.name: mbrWifVcStatTable
mbrWifVcStatTable.description: Table for short and long term VC statistics

mbrWifVcStatEntry.name: mbrWifVcStatEntry
mbrWifVcStatEntry.description: An entry in the VC statistics table. The first of the three integer index values specifies the relative time interval of the statisitics value. Short term stats are measured over a sliding 128-second window. Long term stats are measured over the period specified by the VC's mbrWifVcLongTermStatsInterval. The second index value specifies the MBR X.25 WAN port. The third index value specifies the VC number.

mbrWifVcRcvChars.name: mbrWifVcRcvChars
mbrWifVcRcvChars.description: The number of octets received from this VC during the last stats interval.

mbrWifVcXmtChars.name: mbrWifVcXmtChars
mbrWifVcXmtChars.description: The number of octets transmitted on this VC during the last stats interval.

mbrWifVcRcvX25Pkts.name: mbrWifVcRcvX25Pkts
mbrWifVcRcvX25Pkts.description: The number of X.25 packets received from this VC during the last stats interval.

mbrWifVcXmtX25Pkts.name: mbrWifVcXmtX25Pkts
mbrWifVcXmtX25Pkts.description: The number of X.25 packets transmitted on this VC during the last stats interval.

mbrWifVcRcvCompRatio.name: mbrWifVcRcvCompRatio
mbrWifVcRcvCompRatio.description: The current ratio of raw octets to compressed octets received for this VC. The index values indicate the MBR port number and VC number, respectively.

mbrWifVcXmtCompRatio.name: mbrWifVcXmtCompRatio
mbrWifVcXmtCompRatio.description: The current ratio of raw octets to compressed octets transmitted for this VC. The index values indicate the MBR port number and VC number, respectively.

mbrWifVcRminCompRatio.name: mbrWifVcRminCompRatio
mbrWifVcRminCompRatio.description: The lowest ratio of raw octets to compressed octets received for this VC. The index values indicate the MBR port number and VC number, respectively.

mbrWifVcXminCompRatio.name: mbrWifVcXminCompRatio
mbrWifVcXminCompRatio.description: The lowest ratio of raw octets to compressed octets transmitted for this VC. The index values indicate the MBR port number and VC number, respectively.

mbrWifVcRmaxCompRatio.name: mbrWifVcRmaxCompRatio
mbrWifVcRmaxCompRatio.description: The highest ratio of raw octets to compressed octets received for this VC. The index values indicate the MBR port number and VC number, respectively.

mbrWifVcXmaxCompRatio.name: mbrWifVcXmaxCompRatio
mbrWifVcXmaxCompRatio.description: The highest ratio of raw octets to compressed octets transmitted for this VC. The index values indicate the MBR port number and VC number, respectively.

mbrLifState.name: mbrLifState
mbrLifState.description: This object represents the Spanning Tree Algorithm (STA) state of the port. The values are enumerated for the object mbrWifLinkState. When STA is off, the port may be one of up, down, or disabled. The integer index value indicates the MBR port.

mbrLifMacAddress.name: mbrLifMacAddress
mbrLifMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the LAN card corresponding to this port. The integer index value indicates the MBR port.

mbrLifHardwareRev.name: mbrLifHardwareRev
mbrLifHardwareRev.description: The hardware revision level of the LAN card correspond- ing to this port. The integer index value indicates the MBR port.

mbrLifLongTermStatsInterval.name: mbrLifLongTermStatsInterval
mbrLifLongTermStatsInterval.description: This object represents the current time interval that the MBR is using to track its long term statistics for this port.

mbrLifRingNumber.name: mbrLifRingNumber
mbrLifRingNumber.description: The ring number assigned to the 802.5 LAN that this port is connected to. This object is available in SNMP traps only.

mbrLifStatTable.name: mbrLifStatTable
mbrLifStatTable.description: Table for short and long term LAN statistics

mbrLifStatEntry.name: mbrLifStatEntry
mbrLifStatEntry.description: An entry in the LAN statistics table. The first of the two integer index values specifies the relative time interval of the statistic value. Short term stats are measured over a sliding 128-second window. Long term stats are measured over the period specified by the LAN port's mbrLifLongTermStatsInterval. The second value specifies the MBR LAN port.

mbrLifRcvPkts.name: mbrLifRcvPkts
mbrLifRcvPkts.description: The number of packets received from this WAN port during the last stats interval.

mbrLifFwdPkts.name: mbrLifFwdPkts
mbrLifFwdPkts.description: The number of packets transmitted from this LAN port during the last stats interval.

mbrLifRcvMcastPkts.name: mbrLifRcvMcastPkts
mbrLifRcvMcastPkts.description: The number of multicast packets received from this LAN port during the last stats interval.

mbrLifFwdMcastPkts.name: mbrLifFwdMcastPkts
mbrLifFwdMcastPkts.description: The number of multicast packets forwarded to other ports during the last stats interval.

mbrLifRcvErrPkts.name: mbrLifRcvErrPkts
mbrLifRcvErrPkts.description: The number of packets received with error during the last stats interval.

mbrLifNobufDiscPkts.name: mbrLifNobufDiscPkts
mbrLifNobufDiscPkts.description: The number of received packets discarded due to lack of resources during the last stats interval.

mbrLifXmtPkts.name: mbrLifXmtPkts
mbrLifXmtPkts.description: The number of packets transmitted during the last stats interval.
